ce:section.ce:para:
(1) Steric restriction for nucleophile (H2O) to attack the sulfur atom in PIP based sulfonamide is more than that in MPD based sulfonamide. The nitrogen atom in MPD is in the aromatic ring structure while in PIP, the nitrogen is connected to the carbon atom of cycloaliphatic ring. The bond length for CS, NS and CN
                         are 1.790 Å, 1.696 Å and 1.266 Å, respectively. Therefore, the distance between the two rings in PIP based sulfonamide is 1.266 Å shorter than that of PIP based ones (Fig. 6


                        ). (2) The valence shell electron pair of the nitrogen atom, which is involved in the ring of cycloaliphatic structure (PIP), cannot corporate in resonance to break the SN bond of sulfonamide group while for MPD, due to the presence of the free electron pair, it can easily react. (3) Aliphatic diamines have higher molecular weight PSA compared to aromatic diamines, Therefore, the polymer chains of PIP based PSA are not easily attacked compared to the MPD based ones. (Hoseinpour et al., 2016).
